data.meta_description: Tyree Carlisle (4) Cornerback - TULSA – A three-year letterwinner and two-year starter … in his fourth season … has played in 34 career games and has 16 star...
data.text:
TULSA – A three-year letterwinner and two-year starter … in his fourth season … has played in 34 career games and has 16 starts … has 95 career tackles, four pass breakups and two forced fumbles.

2023 – Played in 11 games in 2023 and started eight games… played in the first eight games, while starting the first seven contests … missed the Charlotte game … had 33 stops and one pass breakup … tallied a career-high nine stops at East Carolina … tallied four tackles at Northern Illinois … recorded four stops and one pass breakup vs. #19 Oklahoma … started vs. UAPB in the opener and had five tackles, including 0.5 TFL for -5 yards.

2022 – Played in and started 10 games … had 44 tackles, two stops for -6 yards and three pass breakups … missed the Cincinnati and USF games … made his first career start in the opener at Wyoming and had seven tackles and one pass breakup… totaled a career-high with eight tackles, 1.5 TFL for -6 yards and two pass breakups at Temple … also tallied five tackles in the Navy, SMU and Houston games.

2021 – Played in all 13 games … had 18 tackles, including 15 solos, and one forced fumble … recorded a season-high three stops vs. Old Dominion in the 2021 Myrtle Beach Bowl … made his first career appearance in the season opener vs. UC Davis and had two tackles … had his first career forced fumble at South Florida.

JUNIOR COLLEGE – Played the 2020 season in the spring of 2021 at Independence Community College.

HIGH SCHOOL – Was a two-year starting running back at Troup County High School … rushed for 1,092 yards, a 5.8 average and 16 touchdowns in his final two seasons … also caught 25 passes for 520 yards and two touchdowns in his prep career … gained 628 yards, a 6.3 average and 10 TDs his senior season.

PERSONAL – Favorite NFL team is the Houston Texans … his favorite movie is Training Day … favorite sports movie is Carter High … lists Training Day as his favorite movie … favorite NFL player is former high school teammate Jamari Thrash … began playing football at age 7 … his favorite book is Manifesting … favorite Netflix series is Power … has three siblings … parents are Kelby Holt and Tereice Carlisle … earned his bachelor’s degree in arts, culture and entertainment management in May 2024.
